1
00:02:15,343 --> 00:02:16,469
Hello.

2
00:02:16,611 --> 00:02:18,579
Okay, sir. Okay.

3
00:02:31,593 --> 00:02:33,891
Raghuveer, You're still awake.

4
00:02:43,605 --> 00:02:44,435
Surprisingly,

5
00:02:44,473 --> 00:02:47,931
For the first time in seven years,
I am seeing you smile.

6
00:02:48,844 --> 00:02:50,334
You will be released tomorrow.

7
00:02:50,378 --> 00:02:51,709
That's why you are happy, isn't it?

8
00:02:53,548 --> 00:02:55,641
I'll be seeing my
sister after a long time.

9
00:02:57,486 --> 00:02:58,919
Can't explain how happy I am.

10
00:02:59,087 --> 00:03:00,850
You really love your sister, Don't you?
- Yes!

11
00:03:01,857 --> 00:03:05,293
In all these years,
you never met your family

12
00:03:05,527 --> 00:03:06,994
Neither did you speak to them,

13
00:03:07,562 --> 00:03:09,257
You're a good man

14
00:03:09,331 --> 00:03:10,992
How you landed up here?

15
00:03:14,469 --> 00:03:16,562
I have spent seven years in this jail.

16
00:03:17,806 --> 00:03:19,831
But, my story dates back even longer.

17
00:03:20,709 --> 00:03:22,370
I was just 11 years old.

18
00:03:22,978 --> 00:03:25,811
I was visiting the temple with
my mother and younger sister.

19
00:03:25,914 --> 00:03:30,351
He's my son Raghuveer
and my daughter Sona.

20
00:03:30,785 --> 00:03:32,878
Please make an offering
in their name, Priest.

21
00:03:32,954 --> 00:03:33,943
Sure dear.

22
00:03:34,923 --> 00:03:39,383
Mom, you promised to
take me to my father.

23
00:03:39,794 --> 00:03:41,318
That's where we're going, son.

24
00:03:41,930 --> 00:03:43,056
Here's the offering.

25
00:03:45,367 --> 00:03:46,834
Won't you offer the coconut, dear?

26
00:03:47,035 --> 00:03:50,061
I completely forgot, Priest.
- Do it now.

27
00:03:50,805 --> 00:03:52,773
'My mother used to say'

28
00:03:52,974 --> 00:03:56,671
'... a rotten coconut brings bad luck.'

29
00:03:57,012 --> 00:03:58,502
'And, that's exactly what happened.'

30
00:03:59,314 --> 00:04:01,043
'My father had married someone else.'

31
00:04:01,316 --> 00:04:04,308
'He humiliated my mother.'
- Get out of here!

32
00:04:04,519 --> 00:04:07,386
'And broke all ties with us.'

33
00:04:10,525 --> 00:04:12,925
'My mother couldn't take this betrayal.'

34
00:04:13,562 --> 00:04:15,792
'She was completely shattered.'

35
00:04:18,033 --> 00:04:20,763
'She kept weeping the
entire day with us in tow.'

36
00:04:21,536 --> 00:04:23,367
'And, left us forever.'

37
00:04:23,438 --> 00:04:26,805
Mother. Mother.

38
00:04:30,946 --> 00:04:32,004
What happened?

39
00:04:33,415 --> 00:04:34,313
Who is she?

40
00:04:34,516 --> 00:04:36,347
She's my mother.

41
00:04:36,418 --> 00:04:38,352
She's dead.
- Dead!

42
00:04:50,599 --> 00:04:52,499
Pay your homage.

43
00:04:53,635 --> 00:04:55,899
Here you go, Priest.
- Bless you.

44
00:04:57,305 --> 00:04:58,602
Stop!

45
00:05:02,410 --> 00:05:04,776
Who put this tomb here?

46
00:05:05,380 --> 00:05:06,904
This field belongs to them.

47
00:05:06,982 --> 00:05:08,381
Why are you bothered?

48
00:05:08,450 --> 00:05:09,781
I own this field.

49
00:05:09,851 --> 00:05:11,785
His mother had taken a loan from me.

50
00:05:11,853 --> 00:05:15,914
So, the council has decided,
I can seize this field.

51
00:05:15,991 --> 00:05:18,482
Get rid of this tomb, now!

52
00:05:18,994 --> 00:05:20,928
I'll repay your debt.

53
00:05:20,996 --> 00:05:23,726
Don't break my mother's tomb.

54
00:05:23,798 --> 00:05:25,925
He says he will repay your debt.

55
00:05:26,334 --> 00:05:27,562
Give him a chance.

56
00:05:29,004 --> 00:05:31,837
At first, his father eloped.

57
00:05:31,973 --> 00:05:33,270
Then his mother died.

58
00:05:33,408 --> 00:05:35,842
He's still a kid. How
will he repay my debt?

59
00:05:35,910 --> 00:05:38,902
He'll plough the field and pay you back.
- Him?

60
00:05:38,980 --> 00:05:40,914
I'll toil day and night.

61
00:05:40,982 --> 00:05:42,882
And repay your entire debt.

62
00:05:42,951 --> 00:05:45,784
Otherwise, I will repay your debt.

63
00:05:45,854 --> 00:05:49,813
Fine. Every year the
involvement should reach me on time.

64
00:05:50,825 --> 00:05:54,386
Its installment, not involvement.
- Whatever.

65
00:05:54,696 --> 00:05:56,288
Let's go.

66
00:05:56,965 --> 00:05:58,330
Sir!

67
00:06:12,313 --> 00:06:13,541
Don't cry, Sona.

68
00:06:41,943 --> 00:06:46,744
Mother used to say, that
star is you and that's me.

69
00:06:53,822 --> 00:06:55,050
Come on.

70
00:06:57,358 --> 00:06:58,325
Come on.

71
00:08:56,477 --> 00:08:57,842
Don't worry, Raghu.

72
00:08:57,912 --> 00:08:59,971
Your sister's going to top her exams.

73
00:09:01,816 --> 00:09:03,249
Break the coconut.

74
00:09:19,868 --> 00:09:21,335
Wow! There's a flower inside.

75
00:09:21,502 --> 00:09:22,935
She's definitely going to excel now.

76
00:09:31,813 --> 00:09:34,611
Sona.

77
00:10:09,617 --> 00:10:11,448
Sona. Your books.

78
00:10:11,519 --> 00:10:13,419
Hey! Be careful.

79
00:10:15,924 --> 00:10:18,950
You know she'll drop
them if you interrupt her.

80
00:10:19,394 --> 00:10:22,386
Gauri, its my exam today,
I won't need them.

81
00:10:22,463 --> 00:10:23,794
Take them along, Sona.

82
00:10:23,865 --> 00:10:25,492
You can score better if you copy.

83
00:10:25,566 --> 00:10:27,659
You're too much.
- Is it?

84
00:10:28,303 --> 00:10:28,997
Let's go.

85
00:10:29,904 --> 00:10:31,633
You remember everything, right?
- Yes.

86
00:10:31,906 --> 00:10:33,339
Concentrate on your studies.

87
00:10:33,441 --> 00:10:34,465
And, do well in your exams.
- Yes.

88
00:10:34,542 --> 00:10:36,976
Why don't you go with her?
- Why?

89
00:10:37,312 --> 00:10:38,939
How many times will you tell her...

90
00:10:39,314 --> 00:10:41,839
..."Do good, do good..."

91
00:10:41,916 --> 00:10:46,080
Hey! A hottie just
boarded the earlier bogie.

92
00:10:47,455 --> 00:10:50,356
Sona's always done well...

93
00:10:52,060 --> 00:10:53,027
Where did he go?

94
00:10:54,529 --> 00:11:00,024
"You've cast a spell on me."

95
00:11:00,368 --> 00:11:03,667
"My heart's fallen for you."

96
00:11:10,645 --> 00:11:11,771
"Baby, I love you."

97
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:13,039
Come on.

98
00:11:13,314 --> 00:11:15,282
"Baby, I love you."

99
00:11:15,350 --> 00:11:19,047
"Baby, I love you."

100
00:11:19,454 --> 00:11:22,048
Nice song. You sound good too.

101
00:11:23,291 --> 00:11:24,986
But teasing girls is wrong.

102
00:11:25,059 --> 00:11:25,718
What did he say?

103
00:11:25,793 --> 00:11:26,657
Wrong!

104
00:11:27,395 --> 00:11:29,386
Who are you to interfere?

105
00:11:29,464 --> 00:11:30,328
Move!

106
00:11:31,799 --> 00:11:32,697
See that!

107
00:11:32,767 --> 00:11:34,496
I'll stab you with this.

108
00:11:35,536 --> 00:11:37,800
What the...

109
00:12:44,806 --> 00:12:46,797
Check... and mate.

110
00:12:48,643 --> 00:12:50,076
Someday I'll definitely beat you.

111
00:12:50,411 --> 00:12:53,471
I'm also waiting for that day.

112
00:12:53,548 --> 00:12:54,606
Hello Uncle.

113
00:12:54,782 --> 00:12:59,947
I heard your sister's taking her college exams.
- Yes.

114
00:13:01,622 --> 00:13:04,523
She's pretty intelligent and smart girl.
- Yes.

115
00:13:10,965 --> 00:13:12,023
Sona.

116
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:14,393
Not again, brother.

117
00:13:16,370 --> 00:13:19,965
Sona, you see those stars in the sky...

118
00:13:20,274 --> 00:13:21,969
That one's me and the other one's you.

119
00:13:22,810 --> 00:13:24,004
Mother used to say that, correct?

120
00:13:24,278 --> 00:13:27,509
That means, after Sona's marriage...

121
00:13:27,748 --> 00:13:30,273
...one of the star will disappear.

122
00:13:30,384 --> 00:13:31,442
Mind your own business.

123
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:32,645
And...

124
00:13:33,488 --> 00:13:35,956
Brother, shall I take the
eggs to the market tomorrow?

125
00:13:36,023 --> 00:13:36,853
Yes.

126
00:13:36,924 --> 00:13:38,653
But be careful.

127
00:13:40,495 --> 00:13:42,429
I didn't say that to her.

128
00:13:43,631 --> 00:13:45,622
You keep dropping stuff.

129
00:13:46,434 --> 00:13:47,958
I dropped it only twice today.

130
00:13:48,503 --> 00:13:52,303
Hello!
- Priest, what brings you here at this hour?

131
00:13:52,373 --> 00:13:57,970
After a long search,
I've found a suitable match for Sona.

132
00:13:58,446 --> 00:14:03,349
He works on a big post
in a big American company.

133
00:14:06,487 --> 00:14:09,854
Then, he'll definitely
take his bride along.

134
00:14:09,924 --> 00:14:12,893
Of course, in a big airplane...

135
00:14:14,662 --> 00:14:16,823
This offer's too big for us.

136
00:14:18,733 --> 00:14:20,257
I don't accept it.

137
00:14:20,535 --> 00:14:24,904
Huh! Anyone else would've
pounced on this opportunity.

138
00:14:27,808 --> 00:14:31,574
I don't want a prince for my sister.

139
00:14:31,779 --> 00:14:32,711
Then?

140
00:14:33,014 --> 00:14:37,041
I want a boy that can stay
here and look after her.

141
00:15:30,871 --> 00:15:33,305
Hey, Ram! Where are you?
- On the beach.

142
00:15:33,374 --> 00:15:34,932
On the beach, with the girls?

143
00:15:35,409 --> 00:15:36,501
All by yourself.

144
00:15:36,577 --> 00:15:37,839
You didn't invite me.

145
00:15:37,912 --> 00:15:40,005
You've become selfish.
- Hello.

146
00:15:40,314 --> 00:15:42,009
Hello.
- Hello.

147
00:15:42,683 --> 00:15:44,776
That's my trick.

148
00:15:44,852 --> 00:15:47,753
This is what I do
when your mom scolds me.

149
00:15:47,822 --> 00:15:49,949
Hello. I can't hear you.
- Okay.

150
00:15:50,024 --> 00:15:52,754
Enjoy yourself. Have fun.
- Thanks, dad.

151
00:15:54,528 --> 00:15:56,655
Wow! He heard this though.

152
00:15:59,567 --> 00:16:01,865
I heard you made a donation...

153
00:16:01,936 --> 00:16:03,267
...to the Royal Australian Orphanage.

154
00:16:03,337 --> 00:16:04,634
It's a petty amount.

155
00:16:04,805 --> 00:16:05,897
10,000 Dollars.

156
00:16:05,973 --> 00:16:08,965
You call that a petty amount.

157
00:16:09,243 --> 00:16:12,508
You could've spent that
money for PR activities.

158
00:16:12,613 --> 00:16:15,013
Could've thrown a party
for your business colleagues.

159
00:16:15,249 --> 00:16:16,944
Think about the profits.

160
00:16:17,285 --> 00:16:19,378
We anyways throw parties.

161
00:16:20,354 --> 00:16:23,755
Stop wasting money on useless things.

162
00:16:24,258 --> 00:16:27,022
You know I don't like it.

163
00:16:33,868 --> 00:16:34,698
Hi, dad.

164
00:16:35,936 --> 00:16:36,903
Bad mood.

165
00:16:37,872 --> 00:16:38,702
Tell me.

166
00:16:41,042 --> 00:16:42,407
I'm your best friend.

167
00:16:43,744 --> 00:16:44,904
Mom yelled at you again?

168
00:16:45,513 --> 00:16:47,447
Thank you very much.
- Why?

169
00:16:47,615 --> 00:16:50,914
For not asking whether
she beat me up or not.

170
00:16:51,652 --> 00:16:53,449
You know how she is,

171
00:16:53,921 --> 00:16:56,947
then, why the long face?
- I'm not upset.

172
00:16:57,992 --> 00:17:00,790
Do you know why the world's
greatest philosopher was happy?

173
00:17:00,828 --> 00:17:03,388
Because he knew how to
tolerate his tormenting wife.

174
00:17:05,433 --> 00:17:06,832
Angry bird!

175
00:17:10,938 --> 00:17:11,632
Hello.

176
00:17:11,706 --> 00:17:12,536
It wasn't for you.

177
00:17:12,573 --> 00:17:14,336
I was talking about Socrates' wife.

178
00:17:14,408 --> 00:17:15,466
Hello, brother-in-law.

179
00:17:15,509 --> 00:17:16,635
Krishnakant speaking.

180
00:17:16,711 --> 00:17:21,842
How are you?
- Trying to get along with your sister.

181
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:23,907
Whats new in that.

182
00:17:25,019 --> 00:17:26,577
It's your brother from India.

183
00:17:26,654 --> 00:17:27,678
Hello.
- Sister.

184
00:17:27,755 --> 00:17:28,915
Yes, brother.
- How are you?

185
00:17:28,989 --> 00:17:31,787
How are you?
- Everything is good.

186
00:17:31,992 --> 00:17:33,391
So what's new?

187
00:17:33,461 --> 00:17:34,985
Too many things, but
the biggest news is...

188
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:39,790
...Ria's getting engaged
on the 14th of this month.

189
00:17:40,401 --> 00:17:41,368
So soon!

190
00:17:41,769 --> 00:17:44,761
Was she in love?
- Exactly.

191
00:17:44,939 --> 00:17:48,636
I objected but she cried,
so I had to agree.

192
00:17:48,676 --> 00:17:50,769
But is the boy from a good family?

193
00:17:52,046 --> 00:17:54,037
I mean, are they rich?

194
00:17:54,315 --> 00:17:56,715
That's exactly why I agreed.

195
00:17:56,784 --> 00:17:57,751
Listen.

196
00:17:57,818 --> 00:17:59,410
Reach here as soon as you can.

197
00:17:59,487 --> 00:18:01,478
Because you only have to
look after the arrangements.

198
00:18:01,589 --> 00:18:02,351
And...

199
00:18:02,390 --> 00:18:03,652
Don't forget to tell brother-in-law.

200
00:18:03,724 --> 00:18:06,557
And...
- Hello, aunt. - Yes, dear

201
00:18:06,627 --> 00:18:09,960
Ria speaking.
- Congratulations. How are you?

202
00:18:10,264 --> 00:18:13,563
Fine, aunt, Bring Ram along too.

203
00:18:13,634 --> 00:18:15,568
We haven't met since our childhood.

204
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:17,297
Sure, dear. Bye.

205
00:18:17,838 --> 00:18:19,999
Ram.
- Yes, mom.

206
00:18:20,274 --> 00:18:21,605
Ram. We're going to India.

207
00:18:21,675 --> 00:18:22,733
India!

208
00:18:23,911 --> 00:18:25,902
India!
- You aren't going.

209
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:28,441
Why?
- You've to attend a conference in US.

210
00:18:28,516 --> 00:18:30,746
Don't you remember?
- Oh yeah.

211
00:18:30,985 --> 00:18:33,010
America, Yo!

212
00:18:34,622 --> 00:18:35,884
Stop!

213
00:18:37,458 --> 00:18:38,618
Brother.

214
00:18:40,728 --> 00:18:42,491
Ria, how are you?

215
00:18:42,563 --> 00:18:44,360
Chocolate for you, brother.

216
00:18:45,599 --> 00:18:47,328
You never forget to get
the chocolate, do you?

217
00:18:47,401 --> 00:18:50,495
Welcome the bride.
- Bride?

218
00:18:50,671 --> 00:18:51,603
When are you getting married?

219
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:56,840
Next Friday. That's just 15 days.
- Right.

220
00:18:56,911 --> 00:18:58,708
And, you are both invited.

221
00:18:58,779 --> 00:18:59,575
Of course.

222
00:18:59,647 --> 00:19:01,012
We'll reach there two days in advance.

223
00:19:01,282 --> 00:19:03,443
Just two days?

224
00:19:03,684 --> 00:19:06,676
I have come here to take Sona right now.

225
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:08,312
Now?
- Of course.

226
00:19:08,389 --> 00:19:10,380
Sona, when would you
expect me to come over...

227
00:19:10,458 --> 00:19:11,584
...for your marriage?

228
00:19:12,660 --> 00:19:14,594
I don't know, ask brother.

229
00:19:15,796 --> 00:19:16,728
Brother!

230
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:22,497
How many days before,
you expect me to come for Sona's marriage?

231
00:19:22,570 --> 00:19:25,300
At least 15 days.
- Right.

232
00:19:25,406 --> 00:19:27,874
My marriage is just 15 days later.

233
00:19:27,942 --> 00:19:29,739
I'm just like your sister.

234
00:19:29,810 --> 00:19:31,710
Please send her along.

235
00:19:31,779 --> 00:19:33,007
Please, brother.

236
00:19:33,247 --> 00:19:34,805
Please.

237
00:19:36,016 --> 00:19:39,281
Actually, I have never
sent her alone anywhere.

238
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:41,283
She has also never
stayed apart from you.

239
00:19:41,355 --> 00:19:43,687
But you will have to send her along.

240
00:19:43,891 --> 00:19:45,017
Please, brother.

241
00:19:45,292 --> 00:19:47,760
Please. Please. Please.

242
00:19:48,796 --> 00:19:50,263
You want to go, Sona?

243
00:19:52,266 --> 00:19:54,700
I won't, if you say no.

244
00:19:56,837 --> 00:19:58,031
Go on.

245
00:20:01,041 --> 00:20:02,338
Be careful!

246
00:21:28,395 --> 00:21:30,386
Hey my coconut, give me my money.

247
00:21:32,800 --> 00:21:34,791
Hey! Hi, I'm Ram.

248
00:21:34,868 --> 00:21:35,800
What's up, beautiful?

249
00:21:35,869 --> 00:21:36,767
May I know your name please?

250
00:21:36,837 --> 00:21:38,634
Paro.
- Hi.

251
00:21:38,706 --> 00:21:40,469
Dad. Mom!

252
00:23:34,855 --> 00:23:35,787
Ram!

253
00:23:36,623 --> 00:23:38,318
Look what a big bouquet
I brought for you.

254
00:23:38,358 --> 00:23:39,757
I... I am Bijli.

255
00:23:46,767 --> 00:23:48,428
Bijli!

256
00:23:51,872 --> 00:23:52,804
Nephew.

257
00:23:52,873 --> 00:23:53,601
Nephew.

258
00:23:53,674 --> 00:23:55,733
Uncle.
- My dear!

259
00:23:56,844 --> 00:23:57,902
Put your leg down.

260
00:23:58,879 --> 00:24:01,313
That's enough.

261
00:24:02,616 --> 00:24:03,947
He's naughty!

262
00:24:08,288 --> 00:24:09,255
What is he doing?

263
00:24:11,859 --> 00:24:12,917
Who is this beauty and the beast?

264
00:24:12,993 --> 00:24:14,756
She's my distant relative.

265
00:24:15,629 --> 00:24:16,027
Her too.

266
00:24:16,296 --> 00:24:16,955
And I'm a close one.

267
00:24:19,366 --> 00:24:19,957
You...

268
00:24:27,374 --> 00:24:28,466
Why aren't you saying anything?

269
00:24:28,976 --> 00:24:32,639
Tell me, even a vegetable vendor
in Australia speak English?

270
